<TITLE> US women thump Cuba to reach final </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BEIJING, Aug 21 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - The United States thumped Cuba 3-0 on Thursday to reach the Olympic women's volleyball final, getting payback when it mattered most for a straight sets loss to the Cubans in the preliminary round. The deflated Cuban squad sobbed in near silence and sat stunned on the bench for several minutes after losing the semi-final 25-20 25-16 25-17. If Athens champions China can beat Brazil later on Thursday it would set up a highly charged repeat of the 1984 final when Chinese-born U.S. coach Jenny Lang Ping helped China win gold in Los Angeles. "After playing Cuba the last time, the team in itself made an agreement that we would never play that level of volleyball ever again," said Kim Willoughby, who scored the three last points with smashes. "I'm just hoping that in two days we play the same style of volleyball and we get the same results." Cuba, who won the bronze medal four years ago, trailed for most of the match on Thursday, struggling with errors. In the third set, Cuba gave the Americans at least four points on serves that failed to get over the net. The U.S. defence was hard to penetrate, too, with multiple strong blocks and difficult digs. "Our reception was very bad, and we made many mistakes in service," said Cuba's coach, Antonio Perdomo Estrella. "With these two elements no good, it is impossible to win.
